<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="391" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-05"><hi rend="italic">February 5,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Griscom reports that warlike preparations are being rushed, and that
                            it seems that the Japanese Government has decided that it <pb facs="0500" n="412" xml:id="pg_412"/> has waited longer for an
                            answer from the Russian Government than is reasonable.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>